The ads are the brainchild of a trio of people opening a new Thai restaurant in the Motor City . 
  They want exposure for their business but also to promote Detroit as an alternative for New Yorkers who feel the city is too expensive . 
  There are four billboards — two in Manhattan and two in Bushwick in Brooklyn — which went up about a month ago . 
  ‘The idea really is to spread the word about Detroit as far as we can ,’ said Courtney Henriette  . 
 